# 🇯🇵 Japanese Holiday Coach — 30-Day Learning Plan

A fully self-contained web app to take you from complete beginner to holiday-ready Japanese speaker in 30 days, with under 30 minutes of study per day.

## ✨ Features

- **30 structured days** across 4 weeks: Survival → Conversations → Deeper Talk → Confidence
- **Interactive vocabulary** — type each word 3× to master it, with instant feedback
- **Live mic pronunciation check** — press 🎤 to start, press again to stop; the app checks if your Japanese was intelligible
- **Audio playback** — press ▶ to hear phrases spoken aloud (uses device TTS with Google Translate TTS as fallback)
- **Furigana** — pronunciation shown above every Japanese character
- **Weekly mini-tests** every 7th day with answers
- **Progress saved** automatically in your browser (works across sessions)
- **Export / Import** your progress as a JSON file to move between devices

## 🚀 Using via GitHub Pages

1. Fork this repository
2. Go to **Settings → Pages**
3. Set source to **main branch / root**
4. Your app will be live at `https://YOUR-USERNAME.github.io/REPO-NAME/japanese_coach.html`

Bookmark that URL on your phone — your progress is saved in the browser's localStorage, so it persists across sessions **as long as you use the same browser on the same device**.

## 💾 Keeping Progress Across Devices

Because this is a static file, there is no server to sync progress. Instead:

- **Same device / browser:** Progress saves automatically — just reopen the URL
- **Moving to a new device:** Tap **💾 Export progress** in the app header, save the `.json` file, open the app on your new device, tap **📂 Import progress**
- **Backup:** Export your progress periodically so you don't lose it if you clear browser data

## 🔊 Audio Notes

The app tries your device's built-in Japanese text-to-speech first. If that doesn't work (common on some Android browsers), it automatically falls back to Google Translate TTS. A small badge in the header tells you which engine is active.

**Best browser:** Chrome on Android or desktop Chrome gives the best speech recognition and TTS support.

For mic features on iOS, use **Safari** (it supports the Web Speech API from iOS 14.5+).

## 🎤 Microphone / Speech Recognition

1. Open the app in Chrome (Android) or Safari (iOS)
2. When you tap 🎤 for the first time, your browser will ask for microphone permission — tap **Allow**
3. Press 🎤 to **start** recording, press again (⏹ STOP) to **finish**
4. The app compares what it heard against the target phrase

If mic access is blocked, go to your browser settings → Site permissions → Microphone → allow for the page.

